Well what i would do is go into “my computer” go into program files and check which update you have like for example if you have update 22 then change jdk1.6.0_21 to
jdk1.6.0_22 and also some computers arent compatable with (x86) so remove it to make it look like this c:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_22\bin\javac.exe

item.title: Compiler issues
item.dc:creator: @Ashton51 Ashton51
item.description:
@Ashton51 wrote:

Go that directory

c:\Program Files (x86)\Java\jdk1.6.0_21\bin\javac.exe

If you cant go through those EXACT files then neither can the compiler.

64-Bit OS have Program Files (x86) so make sure that if you dont have it that you change it to Program Files

Also make sure 1.6.0_21

Is the exact version and patch of jdk you have, if not then change that.
